de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core

Class ResourceDemandType

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.ResourceDemandType

  • public class ResourceDemandType
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a type of a measured resource, like CPU usage or HDD usage.

    For the typical types of a measured resources it is recommended to use one of the constants

    • RESOURCE_TYPE_CPU
    • RESOURCE_TYPE_CPU_NS
    • RESOURCE_TYPE_HDD
    • RESOURCE_TYPE_HDD_NS
    • RESOURCE_TYPE_NETWORK
    • RESOURCE_TYPE_NETWORK_NS
    instead of creating its own instances.

      • ResourceDemandType

        public ResourceDemandType(java.lang.String name,
                          boolean isNs)
        Creates a custom resource type.
        Parameters:
        name - A name which is a unique identifier for this resource type. Must not be null, must not be empty.
        isNs - Whether this resource type is measured machine dependent or not. If it is measured machine dependent, the measurement unit must be ns (nanoseconds).
